Federer won his first and to date only doubles Masters Series 1000 event in Miami with Max Mirnyi[41] and made it to one singles Masters Series 1000 event in Rome on clay, which he lost.[42][43] Federer made it to nine finals on the ATP Tour and won seven of them, including the 500 series events at Dubai and Vienna.[42] Lastly, Federer won the year-end championships over Andre Agassi, finishing the year as world No. 2, narrowly behind Andy Roddick by only 160 points.[42][44]
